== Mac & Cheese ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}.

When the water is boiling, stir in the @macaroni{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, reserve from pasta water, then drain in a #colander{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to prevent it from sticking.

== Fried Chicken ==

While the pasta cooks, crack the @egg{1} into a #medium bowl{} and whisk. Add the @panko breadcrumbs{50%g} into another medium bowl and season with @salt{¼%tsp} and @ground black pepper{}.

Season the @British chicken thighs{3}, then dip it into the bowl with egg and the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely coated.

Shake off the excess and transfer to a clean #plate{}. 
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to coat the bottom of the pan.
> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan and fry until golden-brown, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Transfer the chicken to a #baking tray{} and bake on the middle shelf until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}. 
> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Buffalo Sauce ==

Carefully discard the hot oil from the chicken frying pan and return to medium-high heat.

Add the @cider vinegar{15%ml} and @water{75%ml}, bring to a boil, then simmer until reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir through the @sriracha sauce{30%ml} and @honey{15%ml} until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. 
> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Once thickened, remove from the heat and stir through the @butter{20%g} until melted. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside.

== Blue Mac & Cheese ==

Pop the (now empty) pasta saucepan on medium-high heat. Add the @reserved pasta water{50%ml}, @chicken stock paste{10%g} and cooked macaroni. Bring to the boil, stirring constantly, then remove from the heat.

Vigorously stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @crumbled blue cheese{30%g} until smooth and melted. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Meanwhile, halve the @burger buns{2}. Pop them onto a baking tray and into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

When everything's ready, spread the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} on the bun bases. Cut your chicken thighs in half and arrange on top.

Drizzle over your buffalo sauce, then top with your bun lids and transfer to your plates.

Serve your craft burgers with your blue mac & cheese alongside. Finish with a handful of @wild rocket{20%g} and a drizzle of @balsamic glaze{12%ml} over the leaves.

Enjoy!